Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Ashwin, out Neesham Run Out!! A mix-up and it looks like Ashwin has sacrificed himself. Or at least he's tried to. They're checking with the third umpire to see if they've crossed when the bails are taken off. Okay it doesn't look like they have, so it'll be Neesham who'll have to go. This is driven straight to cover, Neesham takes off but there's no run there. The throw comes in to Bishnoi, Ashwin tries to sacrifice himself but he's late and they don't cross. Commentary Text: Chahal to Hooda, out Stumped!! What happened there? Samson almost messed up the stumping but then Hooda kept looking at the keeper and didn't make much of an effort to come back in to the crease. Then Samson grabbed the ball disloged the bails but just to be sure managed to uproot one of the sticks in case he had missed the ball while trying to stump the batter out. The third umpire had a look and did clarify that Samson had disturbed the sticks the first time with the ball in his hands. Samson had a big smile after all of it happened but it easily could have ended in a frown. The batter danced down, missed the delivery and the ball went off his pads to dribble towards the keeper for him to do the rest. Hooda st Samson b Chahal 59(39) [4s-5 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Ashwin to Krunal Pandya, out Caught by Riyan Parag!! The tag team effort from Buttler-Parag has done it. Buttler did excellently first to clutch it and then lob it to the man coming in from long-off - Parag. Buttler took a mini leap after catching it and then when he thought he will trip over, he released it at the right time. RR get the wicket they needed and it is Ashwin, who is in the middle of a terrific spell who has delivered it. And the lob from Buttler was also so precise that Parag took it easily. Krunal Pandya c Riyan Parag b Ashwin 25(23) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Prasidh to Rahul, out Caught by Jaiswal!! And Prasidh has had the last laugh in this battle within the battle. Now he is not going stop reminding KL of this wicket every time he sees him. Those whatsapp groups could be buzzing too. But this is smart bowling from Prasidh. He didn't want to let KL to play off the front foot after that thumping six. Knows KL has consumed balls and wanting to break free. So he cramps him for room with a back of a length and that cut back in, KL thought he had a back foot drive over point, but he picked out the fielder who took an overhead catch. Glum faces in the LSG ownership group as KL walks off. We came for Boult v KL, but Prasidh v Kl was a lovely battle to watch. Rahul c Jaiswal b Prasidh 10(19) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Boult to de Kock, out Caught by Neesham!! Oh Quinny! He stands there in disbelief. Smashed this cut shot but picks out Neesham at point. It's a low catch. Neesham says he caught it clean, Quinny walks off. But they are checking. "Clearly in the hands" says third ump. Gone! Short of a length swinging away outside off stump, de Kock played the right shot. But he couldn't keep it on the ground and that is a very good catch because it was dying on the fielder. Neesham dived forward and got his hands under it. RR get the early breakthrough. de Kock c Neesham b Boult 7(8) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Prasidh to de Kock, FOUR, what a brilliant straight drive. You show the full face of the bat to the bowler with great balance after a shot when the bowler looks up in his followthrough, that's a statement. Length delivery on the stumps, de Kock stays in his crease and punches it so straight and it rockets for four. Gee, this is a good pitch
